# Goal Description

The current logic (mock data and service-like functions) is mixed with the mobile application. The objective is to move this logic to a professional backend structure at the root of the project (`f:\DigiQC\backend`) using FastAPI. This folder will follow a standard organizational pattern with routes, controllers, services, and models.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Standalone Backend (Python/FastAPI)

Move business logic and data management out of the mobile app and into a well-structured server.

#### [NEW] `backend/app/main.py`
- Main entry point for the FastAPI application.

#### [NEW] `backend/app/models/`
- Pydantic models (schemas) for inspections, reports, and service requests.

#### [NEW] `backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/`
- API routes (e.g., `inspections.py`, `service_requests.py`) following RESTful principles.

#### [NEW] `backend/app/controllers/`
- Controller layer to manage business calculations (e.g., determining final report status).

#### [NEW] `backend/app/services/`
- Service layer for data persistence (currently using a mock-in-memory DB).

***

### [Component] DigiQC-mobile (Refactoring)

#### [MODIFY] `services/*.service.ts`
- Update the existing React Native services to use `fetch()` or `axios` to communicate with the Python backend instead of using the local [mock-db.ts](file:///f:/DigiQC/DigiQC-mobile/services/mock-db.ts).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `uvicorn` to start the backend.
- Use `curl` or Postman to verify endpoints return correct data.

### Manual Verification
- Ensure the mobile app still functions correctly but now fetches its data from the centralized backend server.
